{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Impose a Robin Hood tax on banker bonuses as part of the Covid economic recovery",
        "additional_details": "Rather than once again freezing the pay of much of the public sector, we ask that a very small percentage of the bonuses banks pay their staff is taxed & used to help support the NHS, other public services & green initiatives.\r\n\r\nEven with the most optimistic impact that covid and brexit will have on our economy, we cannot afford to safeguard the populations wellbeing without this tax or similar taxes in function and source.\r\n\r\nThe wellbeing of the population during this time will rely upon the key steps the government takes during the economic  recovery period & proportionality taxing the additional bonus income of those in banking is one of them.",
        "background": "The debate isn\u2019t if the Robin Hood tax should be implemented, it\u2019s why hasn\u2019t it been implemented already.",
